Protecting Your Personal Information
UKG Inc. and its
respective affiliates
(collectively, “UKG”, “we” and/or “us”) are committed to protecting the privacy of the individuals who visit our website and subpages located at
https://www.ukg.com/
(the “Site”) and who use our products and services or otherwise interact with us directly (“you”).
SCOPE
This Global Privacy Notice (“Privacy Notice”) describes UKG’s privacy practices in connection with your use of the Site and your use of UKG products and services offered by UKG to its customers and provided for you (collectively, our “Services”). We provide information about the choices you have regarding the collection or use of your personal information including similar terms as defined by various jurisdictions, and the rights provided to you, including the ability to access or update your personal information.
Some data protection laws distinguish between “controllers” and “processors” when it comes to handling personal information. Although the specific terms might vary from one jurisdiction to another, the underlying principles generally stay consistent. The entity that determines the purpose and means of processing of personal data is the controller. The processor is an entity that handles personal information under the instruction of a controller without making decisions. Depending on the scenario, UKG can be either a controller or a processor.
This Privacy Notice applies when UKG is a controller of your personal data (when UKG collects data directly from you). This Privacy Notice describes how UKG processes such data, including collecting, sharing, using, retaining your personal information, and your data subject rights.
This Privacy Notice does not apply to UKG’s data processing activities on behalf of its enterprise customers. If you are an employee, contractor, or job applicant of an organization that uses UKG’s products and services, please contact your employer for any privacy related inquiries. Additionally, this Privacy Notice does not cover:
UKG’s processing of personal information in connection with certain direct-to-consumer products and services (e.g., e-Vault) where UKG is data controller. For more information on UKG’s practices for these products and services, please see the
UKG Employee Vault Notice
.
UKG's processing of personal information as a data processor when providing its Services to UKG's business customers
For more information about biometric data and UKG’s timekeeping devices,
click here
.
Children and/or Minors. Our Services are neither designed nor intended for any users under the legal working age according to the applicable law. If you have any reason to believe that a user of our Site or our services is under the legal working age, please contact us at
Privacy@ukg.com
and we will take appropriate action.
Please refer to our
ESG Program – Privacy and Data Protection
page to learn more about UKG's commitment to privacy.
What is Personal Information?
For purposes of this Privacy Notice, “personal information” means information collected by UKG relating to an identified or identifiable natural person and includes similar terms as defined by various jurisdictions.
Personal information does not include non-personal data such as information that has been aggregated, de-identified, or anonymized so that no individual natural person can reasonably be identified.
Our Role
UKG Inc is the controller of your personal information when you browse our Site or contact us as a prospective customer of our products and services. This means that we determine and are responsible for how your personal information is used.
If you are an end user of our products and services (“End User”), we process your personal information as a data processor on behalf of the relevant customer or as a
subprocessor
on behalf of the UKG affiliate who contracted with the relevant customer except to the extent you are using certain direct-to-consumer products and services (e.g., e-Vault, ). The customer will normally be your current, past, or prospective employer. This means that the UKG customer determines and is responsible for how your personal information is used, and we use your personal information on behalf of the relevant customer based on their instructions, as set out in a data processing agreement between UKG and UKG customer.
We do, however, also use certain personal information of End Users of our Services for our own purposes as a data controller, as described in this Privacy Notice.
Links to Non-UKG Websites
For your convenience, the Site may contain links to third-party websites and/or information. When you access those links, you leave UKG’s Site and are redirected to a third-party website. UKG does not control third-party websites, thus the privacy practices of third parties might differ from UKG’s privacy practices. We do not endorse or make any representations about third-party websites. When you share personal information with third-party websites, the third-party processing is not covered by this Privacy Notice. We encourage you to review the privacy policy of any website or company before sharing personal information.
HOW UKG COLLECTS YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION
Sources of Personal information and Personal Information we Collect:
UKG collects personal information from several different sources, including:
Directly from you as a user of our Services, including job applicants;
From service providers or other third parties, including our customer’s account administrators; and
Automatically from a website visitor’s visit or activity on our Services.
Please review each of the sections below to learn more about how UKG collects personal information, and what personal information is collected.
How We Collect Personal Information
UKG collects personal information when you visit our Services and when you choose to provide personal information. For example, we collect information when you contact us via our Site, provide your email, phone number or other similar contact information, such as the information that you provide when you sign up for a webinar. Job candidates who complete an application for employment with UKG or create a profile on this Site may also provide credentials and other information relevant to the job application.
