HOW UKG USES PERSONAL INFORMATION
Why We Use Your Personal Information:
UKG relies on lawful bases, such as Performance of Contract or Legitimate Interest. Additionally, we may process personal information for the following purposes:
To fulfill the purpose(s) for which the information was collected or provided, including to communicate with you and respond to your inquiries and requests;
To improve our Services, through testing, research, analysis and product development (including Usage Data and, where instructed, aggregate, de-identified or anonymized End User or Customer Content);
To market, advertise, and promote our Services, such as to make suggestions and recommendations to you about products or services that may be of interest to you;
To provide support and information about our Services via virtual assistant, also known as chatbot, available 24/7 on our Sites;
To provide training related to the Services, such as making available training materials or events (whether in-person or online) for which we may use your personal information to provide notices and information regarding such training and events;
For security, audit, internal investigation, and fraud prevention purposes, such as to prevent unauthorized access or disclosure, to maintain data accuracy, to protect the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of your personal information; to allow only the appropriate use of your personal information; to identify any fraudulent, harmful, unauthorized, unethical or illegal activity;
To manage litigation, such as in connection with establishing, exercising, or defending our legal rights where it is necessary for our legitimate interests or the legitimate interests of others;
To improve the content and format of our Services, including by using cookies and other similar technologies, such as to measure the preferences of our Site visitors, analyze trends, administer the Services, analyze use of the Services, and to gather demographic information about visitors to the Site;
To allow us to better understand the functionality of our mobile applications, though we do not link the usage information we collect through the mobile applications to any personal information you submit within the mobile application;
For other purposes for you have provided consent;
To aggregate or deidentify your personal information so that the information can no longer be linked to you or your device and use and share such data for any business purpose in accordance with applicable law; and
To comply with all applicable legal obligations, such as to comply with subpoenas and other court orders to process data where we have determined there is a legal requirement to do so.
No mobile information or SMS consent will be sold or shared with third parties for marketing/promotional purposes.
WHEN UKG DISCLOSES YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION
Please note, UKG does not sell personal information to third parties. The term “sell” as defined by applicable laws, means disclosure of personal information to third parties for monetary or other valuable consideration.
Please review each of the sections below to learn more about how we may share your personal information.
Affiliates:
We may disclose your personal information to our Affiliates in order to facilitate delivery of a product or service or complete a task that you requested.
Third Parties (Vendors/Service Providers):
We may engage with third parties (vendors and/or service providers) to facilitate delivery of a product or service (or perform certain functions such as enhancing and/or delivering our product and service offerings); complete a task that you requested; provide training; support product research and development (including training AI models), conduct marketing and advertising; operate, secure, and optimize the Services; and coordinate and work with our partners.
We have contracts with such third parties to perform certain functions on our behalf, and only at our direction. These third parties are bound by agreements that contain confidentiality and other data protection terms designed to ensure the third parties only use your personal information to the extent necessary to provide these contracted services in accordance with our instructions (and for the purposes we disclose).
Additional Disclosures
We may disclose your personal information as necessary to:
To provide customer service or technical support regarding training or webinars for which you register or attend;
For our administration, and business operation purposes and to keep a record of your relationship with us;
Comply with the law or with legal obligations, such as with law enforcement officials, government authorities or other third parties in response to a lawful request for information by a competent authority, if we believe disclosure is in accordance with, or is otherwise required by, any applicable law, regulation, or legal process, including to meet national security or law enforcement requirements;
To manage litigation and conduct internal audits and investigations, such as to protect and defend our rights and property, investigate fraudulent or illegal activity, and conduct internal financial, security, or other audits;
Protect against misuse or unauthorized use of our Site, products, and services;
Protect the personal safety or property of our users or the public (among other things, this means that if you provide false information or attempt to use another’s identity, information about you may be disclosed as part of any investigation into your actions)
In connection with, or during the negotiation of, any merger, sale of company assets, consolidation or restructuring, financing or acquisition of all or a portion of our business by or to another company, including the transfer of contact information and data of customers, partners, and end users; • In an aggregated and de-identified or anonymized form; and
When we have your consent to share the information.
Other than as stated in this Privacy Notice, we will endeavor not to release your personal information to unknown or unaffiliated third parties, and we will not cross-reference your personal information with that of any other customer or entity.
TRANSFERRING PERSONAL INFORMATION
International Transfers
UKG agrees it will use the Standard Contractual Clauses (“SCCs”) or the UK International Data Transfer Agreement for UKG transfers to third-party
subprocessors
subject to cross border mechanisms for transfers between UKG entities.
UKG agrees it will use the Standard Contractual Clauses (“SCCs”) or the UK International Data Transfer Agreement for UKG transfers to third-party subprocessors subject to cross border mechanisms for transfers between UKG entities. For recipients in the US, UKG may also transfer personal information to recipients who have certified to the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework, Swiss-US Data Privacy Framework and the UK-U.S. Data Privacy Framework. This practice complies with European requirements for transfers or processing of personal information by UKG outside the EEA, Switzerland, and the UK or in a jurisdiction other than the EEA, Switzerland, UK or other European Commission-approved countries providing ‘adequate’ data protection. To learn more about how UKG complies with the Schrems II caselaw, please refer to UKG’s
Transfer Risk and Impact Statement
.
Data Privacy Framework
UKG and its
subsidiaries
comply with the EU-U.S. and the Swiss-US Data Privacy Framework as well as the UK-U.S. Data Privacy Framework (collectively, the "Data Privacy Framework"), including liability for onward transfers, as set forth by the U.S. Department of Commerce regarding the collection, use, and retention of personal information transferred from the European Union, the United Kingdom and/or Switzerland, as applicable. UKG has certified to the Department of Commerce that it adheres to the Data Privacy Framework Principles with respect to such information. If there is any conflict between the terms in this notice and the Data Privacy Framework Principles, the Data Privacy Framework Principles shall govern. To learn more about the Data Privacy Framework program, and to view our certification, please visit the
Data Privacy Framework
website and
UKG’s Data Privacy Framework Statement
In compliance with the EU-U.S. DPF and the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF and the Swiss-U.S. DPF, UKG commits to cooperate and comply respectively with the advice of the panel established by the EU data protection authorities (DPAs) and the UK Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO) and the Swiss Federal Data Protection and Information Commissioner (FDPIC) with regard to unresolved complaints concerning our handling of human resources data received in reliance on the EU-U.S. DPF and the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF and the Swiss-U.S. DPF in the context of the employment relationship.
Data processed:
UKG provides HR management tools that our customers use for their workforce. In providing these tools, UKG processes data our customers submit to our services or instruct us to process on their behalf. While UKG’s customers decide what data is processed, it typically includes information about their employees such as contact information, scheduling, and pay slips. Purposes of data processing: UKG processes data submitted by customers for the purpose of providing UKG’s online services to our customers. To fulfill these purposes, UKG may access the data to provide the services, to correct and address technical or service problems, to respond to customer support matters, or to follow customer instructions who submitted the data, in response to contractual requirements or for security monitoring.
Inquiries and complaints:
If you believe UKG maintains your personal data in one of the services within the scope of our Data Privacy Framework certification, you may direct any inquiries or complaints concerning our Data Privacy Framework compliance to
privacy@ukg.com
. UKG will respond within 45 days. If you have an unresolved privacy or data use concern that we have not addressed satisfactorily, please contact our U.S.-based third-party dispute resolution provider (free of charge) at
https://feedback-form.truste.com/watchdog/request
. If neither UKG nor our dispute resolution provider resolves your complaint, you may have the possibility to engage in binding arbitration through the Data Privacy Framework Panel. For more information on this option, please see Annex I of the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework Principles.
Third parties who may receive personal data:
UKG uses a limited number of third-party service providers to assist us in providing our services to customers. These third-party providers offer various services, including data storage services. These third-parties may access, process, or store personal data in the course of providing their services. UKG maintains contracts with these third parties restricting their access, use and disclosure of personal data in compliance with our Data Privacy Framework obligations, including the onward transfer provisions, and UKG remains responsible and liable if they fail to meet those obligations and we are responsible for the event giving rise to damage.
Your rights to access, to limit use, and to limit disclosure:
EU individuals and Swiss individuals have rights to access personal data about them, and to limit use and disclosure of their personal data. With our Data Privacy Framework self-certification, UKG has committed to respect those rights. Except for MyPeopleDoc Employee Vault and Immedis Tax Services, UKG personnel have limited ability to access data our customers submit to our services. If you wish to request access, or to limit use, or to limit disclosure, please provide the name of the customer who submitted your data to our services. We will refer your request to that customer and will support them as needed in responding to your request.
U.S. Federal Trade Commission enforcement:
The Federal Trade Commission has jurisdiction over UKG’s compliance with the Data Privacy Framework and is subject to the investigatory and enforcement powers of The Federal Trade Commission
Compelled disclosure:
UKG may be required to disclose personal information in response to lawful requests by public authorities, including to meet national security or law enforcement requirements. UKG maintains transparency reports accordingly.
AP
UKG’s privacy practices, described in this Privacy Notice, comply with the APEC Cross Border Privacy Rules System (CBPR). The APEC CBPR system provides a framework for organizations to ensure the protection of Personal Information transferred among participating APEC economies. More information about the APEC framework can be found here.
RETAINING PERSONAL INFORMATION
UKG will only retain personal information for the length of time necessary to fulfill the purpose(s) for which the information was collected or as required or permitted by applicable laws, (including the resolution of disputes) and in accordance with our customer contracts.
To determine the appropriate retention period for personal information, we consider the amount, nature, and sensitivity of the personal information, the potential risk of harm from unauthorized use or disclosure of the personal information, the purposes for which we process your personal information, and whether we can achieve those purposes through other means, and the applicable legal requirements.
When we no longer require your personal information, we will either delete or deidentify it or, if this is not possible, we will securely store it in accordance with this Privacy Notice and cease use of the personal information until deletion is possible. If we deidentify your personal information (so that it is no longer associated with you), we may retain this information for longer periods.
DATA SUBJECT RIGHTS
In accordance with applicable law and depending on your location, you may be entitled to exercise some or all the following rights regarding our collection, use, and sharing of your personal information:
Access the personal information we maintain about you;
Update or correct any inaccurate or incomplete personal information about you;
Request that we delete your personal information;
Restrict the processing of your personal information;
Receive the personal information you have previously provided to UKG, in a machine-readable format, allowing you to transfer that personal information to another company at your discretion;
Not be subject to a decision based solely on automated processing, including profiling, which produces legal effects concerning you or similarly significantly affects you; and
Dispute resolution
You also have the right to object to our use of your personal information in certain circumstances. There may be compelling reasons for continuing to process your personal information, and we will assess and inform you if that is the case. You can object to marketing activities for any reason.
Exercising Your Rights
To protect your privacy and security, we take reasonable steps to verify your identity before granting access to your personal information. Please follow the instructions below based on your relationship with UKG and provide the requested information to allow us to adequately address your request. We will respond to your request within a reasonable timeframe and as otherwise required by applicable law in your location.
If you are not a California resident and would like to request access to your personal information or request erasure (right to be forgotten) of personal information previously provided, please contact
privacy@ukg.com
.
